-- London Police Start Probe Into Soccer Referee’s Alleged Comments
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-10-30T13:12:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-30/london-police-start-probe-into-soccer-referee-s-alleged-comments.html
London ’s Metropolitan Police said
they launched an investigation into alleged comments by referee
Mark Clattenburg during the Premier League match between Chelsea
and Manchester United two days ago.  Chelsea complained to soccer authorities that Clattenburg
made “inappropriate” comments to two of its players. He denies
the allegation, Sky Sports reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  